Question

Which graph shows a \(\frac{22\pi}{5}\) angle in standard position?

Solution

The given angle is \(\frac{22\pi}{5}\). The angle is positive, so the angle rotates counterclockwise.

Each wedge shown below corresponds to an angle of \(\frac{\pi}{5}\). So, we just need to turn across 22 wedges counterclockwise.
